Program: Great Lives
Title: John H Hammond
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b055fzbs
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 13 May 2016
In a career that stretched from 1932 to 1985, legendary record producer John Hammond discovered Billie Holiday, Bob Dylan, Aretha Franklin and Bruce Springsteen. He also worked tirelessly to end race discrimination in the music industry. Record producer Joe Boyd discusses Hammond's career with Matthew Parris and with Dunstan Prial, author of a new biography of Hammond. Show less